text: Maui County, officially the County of Maui, is a county in the U.S. state of Hawaii. As of the 2020 census, 164,754 people lived there. The county seat is Wailuku. It consists of the islands of Maui, Lanai, Molokai (except for a part of Molokai that comprises Kalawao County), Kahoolawe, and Molokini. ==References== Category:1905 establishments in Hawaii Category:Hawaii counties
